 if you're going to track these tactics

1049
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:38,140
 is that false teachers will prey on guilty consciences.

1050
00:43:38,140 --> 00:43:41,400
 These women that Paul's speaking of,

1051
00:43:41,400 --> 00:43:43,840
 they were burdened with sins is what he's saying.

1052
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:46,440
 And so the idea there is that they have a shame complex.

1053
00:43:46,440 --> 00:43:47,960
 They have done things they shouldn't.

1054
00:43:47,960 --> 00:43:51,220
 And so now, because they are ashamed of their behavior,

1055
00:43:51,220 --> 00:43:55,680
 they have a sense of spiritual inferiority to these men

1056
00:43:55,680 --> 00:43:57,920
 who are teaching them,

1057
00:43:57,920 --> 00:44:01,700
 who seem to be the godly sort of representative.

1058
00:44:01,700 --> 00:44:03,320
 And yet what you need to know

1059
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:05,680
 is why this is so important to understand

1060
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:07,080
 that in the gospel,

1061
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:11,880
 you're liberated from both the penalty and the power of sin.

1062
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:14,240
 That that's the glory of the good news of Christ

1063
00:44:14,240 --> 00:44:17,400
 is that you're no longer trying to overcome your sin

1064
00:44:17,400 --> 00:44:19,660
 for it has been overcome.

1065
00:44:19,660 --> 00:44:21,520
 I remember sitting with a dear friend of mine

1066
00:44:21,520 --> 00:44:24,260
 whenever I lived in College Station, Texas,

1067
00:44:24,260 --> 00:44:25,960
 and he was struggling with pornography.

1068
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:28,800
 And so we're praying through a recent misstep

1069
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:29,640
 that he had made.

1070
00:44:29,640 --> 00:44:31,320
 And he was, I'll just never forget it.

1071
00:44:31,320 --> 00:44:32,160
 He was praying.

1072
00:44:32,160 --> 00:44:35,840
 He was like, "Jesus, would you help me to beat my sin?"

1073
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:37,040
 And then he stopped.

1074
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:43,600
 And he prayed instead, "No, you've already beat that sin.

1075
00:44:43,600 --> 00:44:44,880
 It's already defeated.

1076
00:44:44,880 --> 00:44:47,600
 It's already dead and in the ground.

1077
00:44:47,600 --> 00:44:48,520
 You've overcome it.

1078
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:52,480
 So would you help me to live like it?"

1079
00:44:52,480 --> 00:44:55,060
 And I thought that was so powerful

1080
00:44:55,060 --> 00:44:57,180
 because he understood the gospel

1081
00:44:57,180 --> 00:44:59,880
 as he was applying it to his life.

1082
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:02,440
 And when we got up off the ground, rose from our knees,

1083
00:45:02,440 --> 00:45:03,920
 that brother was light.

1084
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:06,200
 Like there was a sense of freedom in him.

1085
00:45:06,200 --> 00:45:10,080
 How do you feel whenever you confess your sins to Jesus?

1086
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:12,320
 Like, are you filled with relief by the end of it?

1087
00:45:12,320 --> 00:45:14,700
 Are you filled with regret and remorse?

1088
00:45:14,700 --> 00:45:16,200
 I'm not saying that you shouldn't feel regret

1089
00:45:16,200 --> 00:45:18,040
 or remorse for your sin.

1090
00:45:18,040 --> 00:45:20,140
 We know godly grief leads to repentance.

1091
00:45:20,140 --> 00:45:22,420
 Paul tells us that, but what you need to know

1092
00:45:22,420 --> 00:45:23,800
 is that when you get up,

1093
00:45:23,800 --> 00:45:27,660
 the gospel is transformative to the spiritual state.

1094
00:45:27,660 --> 00:45:29,040
 It impacts your soul.

1095
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:30,800
 It changes your eternity

1096
00:45:30,800 --> 00:45:34,000
 and it should liberate you into a kind of lightness

1097
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:36,740
 that leads you to move on.

1098
00:45:36,740 --> 00:45:40,400
 The fourth thing they'll do is they'll appeal

1099
00:45:40,400 --> 00:45:41,320
 to aimlessness.

1100
00:45:41,320 --> 00:45:42,640
 That's what Paul means when he says,

1101
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:45,680
 "They were led astray by various passions."

1102
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:48,880
 These women in this story, but it's true for all of us.

1103
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:52,680
 If we are uncertain of our purpose in life,

1104
00:45:52,680 --> 00:45:55,120
 then we have no sense of permanence

1105
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:58,480
 to stay focused in that general direction.

1106
00:45:58,480 --> 00:46:01,040
 Like, we'll follow whatever impulse we have.

1107
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:02,840
 And so if someone appeals to something that we like,

1108
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:03,960
 we're gonna chase that down.

1109
00:46:03,960 --> 00:46:05,400
 If someone catches our feelings,

1110
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:07,040
 we're gonna go after that instead.

1111
00:46:07,040 --> 00:46:08,400
 That's what happens here.

1112
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:11,160
 These women, they're aimless.

1113
00:46:11,160 --> 00:46:14,600
 It says that they have various passions.

1114
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:16,600
 And so, so long as one of these false teachers

1115
00:46:16,600 --> 00:46:18,720
 can engage one of those passions,

1116
00:46:18,720 --> 00:46:21,760
 they can lure one of these people away.

1117
00:46:21,760 --> 00:46:22,600
 The same is true for you.

1118
00:46:22,600 --> 00:46:26,040
 You're going to have passion in life.

1119
00:46:26,040 --> 00:46:28,840
 What I would tell you is let them not be varying.

1120
00:46:28,840 --> 00:46:31,320
 Let them be unifying towards the purpose

1121
00:46:31,320 --> 00:46:34,360
 of knowing God and making Him known.

1122
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:37,280
 Like, let that reality that your purpose

1123
00:46:37,280 --> 00:46:39,640
 is to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.

1124
00:46:39,640 --> 00:46:42,220
 Let that be the thing that you pursue

1125
00:46:42,220 --> 00:46:44,800
 for the rest of your days.

1126
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:47,120
 And then the last thing is they seek to persuade.

1127
00:46:47,120 --> 00:46:48,120
 That's what they'll do.

1128
00:46:48,120 --> 00:46:48,960
 They seek to persuade.

1129
00:46:48,960 --> 00:46:49,800
 That's their goal.

1130
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:52,560
 They want to persuade people that are, quote,

1131
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:54,360
 "Always learning, but never able

1132
00:46:54,360 --> 00:46:56,360
 "to come to the knowledge of the truth."

1133
00:46:56,360 --> 00:46:59,520
 You see, false teachers,

1134
00:46:59,520 --> 00:47:03,680
 they want to convince you that the Bible's been corrupted.

1135
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:07,400
 Like, oh man, that's an archaic text.

1136
00:47:07,400 --> 00:47:08,640
 It's got some good ideas,

1137
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:10,720
 but you really shouldn't trust it.

1138
00:47:10,720 --> 00:47:12,720
 Or they want to convince you that something

1139
00:47:12,720 --> 00:47:17,200
 as controversial as homosexuality isn't even in the Bible.

1140
00:47:17,200 --> 00:47:19,280
 So I don't know why we're referencing the scripture

1141
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:21,960
 as a point of proof to that topic.

1142
00:47:21,960 --> 00:47:23,920
 They're going to want to speak to you in a way

1143
00:47:23,920 --> 00:47:26,600
 that convinces you Jesus is just a man.

1144
00:47:26,600 --> 00:47:28,240
 Man, He's a moral example.

1145
00:47:28,240 --> 00:47:30,320
 He was a powerful revolutionary.

1146
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:32,900
 He was someone even that might've performed miracles,

1147
00:47:32,900 --> 00:47:35,400
 but I don't know that He's the Son of God.

1148
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:36,240
 Like, that feels crazy.

1149
00:47:36,240 --> 00:47:38,020
 It doesn't say that anywhere in this book.

1150
00:47:38,020 --> 00:47:41,840
 No, it does in fact say that in this book.

1151
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:43,000
 They're going to want to convince you

1152
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:48,000
 that you shouldn't apply old truth to modern problems.

1153
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:52,660
 Why would you reference something so old and outdated

1154
00:47:52,660 --> 00:47:54,000
 when we have all this new science

1155
00:47:54,000 --> 00:47:56,640
 and all of this brooding evidence?

1156
00:47:56,640 --> 00:47:58,040
 Like, there are new things today

1157
00:47:58,040 --> 00:47:59,680
 that can solve the problems of today.

1158
00:47:59,680 --> 00:48:02,080
 You don't need to look into this book,

1159
00:48:02,080 --> 00:48:04,480
 but you need to know this is a timeless text,

1160
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:07,420
 one that's not archaic in any kind of way.

1161
00:48:07,420 --> 00:48:13,000
 So what do you do when you're confronted

1162
00:48:13,000 --> 00:48:14,360
 with these kinds of people?

1163
00:48:14,360 --> 00:48:18,960
 This is where we'll end, because I'm out of time.

1164
00:48:19,420 --> 00:48:21,580
 (tapping)

1165
00:48:21,580 --> 00:48:25,220
 What do you do when you're confronted

1166
00:48:25,220 --> 00:48:26,520
 with these kind of people?

1167
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:30,200
 You hold fast to the gospel.

1168
00:48:30,200 --> 00:48:35,700
 You cling to the truth that you know.

1169
00:48:35,700 --> 00:48:41,740
 And the truth is, they may make you out to look like a fool

1170
00:48:41,740 --> 00:48:44,140
 because they're smarter than you.

1171
00:48:44,140 --> 00:48:45,460
 They may make you look,

1172
00:48:45,460 --> 00:48:48,660
 they may make you out to look so ignorant

1173
00:48:48,660 --> 00:48:51,440
 because they've done more research than you.

1174
00:48:51,440 --> 00:48:53,420
 But you cling to what you know,

1175
00:48:53,420 --> 00:48:57,220
 because even an ounce of this truth

1176
00:48:57,220 --> 00:49:00,860
 is truer than anything they might tell you.

1177
00:49:00,860 --> 00:49:03,240
 You hold fast to Him.

1178
00:49:03,240 --> 00:49:06,480
 You don't follow them, you follow Christ.

1179
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:11,940
 Because ultimately, He came for you.

1180
00:49:11,940 --> 00:49:17,860
 It's such a powerful thought.

1181
00:49:18,460 --> 00:49:22,420
 That the last days,

1182
00:49:22,420 --> 00:49:26,940
 they were commenced at the coming of Christ.

1183
00:49:26,940 --> 00:49:29,500
 So that as we live through these days,

1184
00:49:29,500 --> 00:49:33,180
 we can always call back to Him and find our hope,

1185
00:49:33,180 --> 00:49:35,780
 find our assurance, find our truth

1186
00:49:35,780 --> 00:49:38,360
 in the midst of a confusing and chaotic world.

1187
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:43,100
 Some of you don't know Him here.

1188
00:49:43,100 --> 00:49:45,300
 I'm praying you would.

1189
00:49:45,300 --> 00:49:46,980
 I'm praying that you wouldn't journey

1190
00:49:46,980 --> 00:49:49,300
 through these difficult days on your own,

1191
00:49:49,300 --> 00:49:51,020
 but you would journey through a God

1192
00:49:51,020 --> 00:49:54,940
 that traversed every known difficulty to get to you.

1193
00:49:54,940 --> 00:49:59,860
 I'm praying that you wouldn't face

1194
00:49:59,860 --> 00:50:03,020
 the dangers ahead by yourself,

1195
00:50:03,020 --> 00:50:06,620
 but you would do so with a King

1196
00:50:06,620 --> 00:50:09,800
 who has faced all known danger,

1197
00:50:09,800 --> 00:50:14,800
 that great danger in sin and death, so victoriously.

1198
00:50:16,740 --> 00:50:17,980
 And I'm praying that you wouldn't try

1199
00:50:17,980 --> 00:50:20,260
 to stand by your own strength,

1200
00:50:20,260 --> 00:50:21,580
 but you would stand with Him,

1201
00:50:21,580 --> 00:50:26,580
 He who stood strong enough while all alone,

1202
00:50:26,580 --> 00:50:30,180
 and He will stand strong enough with you wherever you are.

1203
00:50:30,180 --> 00:50:33,140
 If you don't know Jesus, this is the appropriate place,

1204
00:50:33,140 --> 00:50:35,820
 the right time to come to know Him

1205
00:50:35,820 --> 00:50:37,340
 because He wants to know you.

1206
00:50:37,340 --> 00:50:38,300
 Let me pray that you would.

1207
00:50:38,300 --> 00:50:39,920
 Jesus, thanks for tonight.

1208
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:41,360
 Thanks for this text.

1209
00:50:41,360 --> 00:50:46,180
 I've felt even God, just some intimidation in my own life,

1210
00:50:46,180 --> 00:50:49,140
 thinking about teaching on false teaching,

1211
00:50:49,140 --> 00:50:51,920
 knowing that, man, it can feel inaccessible,

1212
00:50:51,920 --> 00:50:55,420
 but God, I just pray that the people in this room,

1213
00:50:55,420 --> 00:50:57,020
 God, and as I look out at them,

1214
00:50:57,020 --> 00:50:59,540
 I pray for the people in this room,

1215
00:50:59,540 --> 00:51:02,260
 every one of them all across the spectrum of spirituality,

1216
00:51:02,260 --> 00:51:03,860
 some having amazing days

1217
00:51:03,860 --> 00:51:05,700
 and some that are having horrible days,

1218
00:51:05,700 --> 00:51:08,020
 but every one of them here, God,

1219
00:51:08,020 --> 00:51:10,280
 I pray they would know the relevance of this,

1220
00:51:10,280 --> 00:51:14,660
 that the days, they're dark,

1221
00:51:15,660 --> 00:51:18,660
 but we don't have to face the darkness alone

1222
00:51:18,660 --> 00:51:21,140
 for the light of the world has come.

1223
00:51:21,140 --> 00:51:23,820
 May we cling to you, Jesus, who is the way

1224
00:51:23,820 --> 00:51:26,460
 when there was no way,

1225
00:51:26,460 --> 00:51:29,620
 who is the truth in a world filled with lies,

1226
00:51:29,620 --> 00:51:32,460
 and who is the life for those that have none.

1227
00:51:32,460 --> 00:51:34,580
 We love you, and we sing to you now.

1228
00:51:34,580 --> 00:51:36,320
 It's in your name, amen.

